<paragraph blockId="19.[813,1455,810,970]" box="[813,903,810,836]" pageId="19" pageNumber="276">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[813,1455,810,970]" pageId="19" pageNumber="276">
Perrier’s 
<typeStatus box="[907,954,843,869]" pageId="19" pageNumber="276">type</typeStatus>
specimen shares all the characteristics of the common Indian Ocean species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perrier" authorityYear="1869" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1169,1393,876,902]" class="Asteroidea" family="Echinasteridae" genus="Echinaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spinulosida" pageId="19" pageNumber="276" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="purpureus">
<emphasis box="[1169,1393,876,902]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="276">Echinaster purpureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, having a reticulated skeleton and abactinal plates arranged in longitudinal series.
</paragraph>
